oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Intersection of Deaderick STreet and 3rd Avenue North, c.1950s
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Photograph of the intersection of Deaderick Street and 3rd Avenue North, circa late 1950s/early 1960s. Visible buildings include the War Memorial Building, the Cotton States building, and (partially) the Andrew Jackson Hotel. Photographed by the Nashville Housing Authority. Forms part of the MDHA Photograph Collection. 1 photograph : color
